        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1861-08-08T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1861-08-08T00:00:00-05:00" n="174" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d174">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Seward</persName> to Mr. <persName type="to">Schurz</persName>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 18.]</seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/>
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>,</placeName>
                        <date calendar="gregorian" when="1861-08-08">
                            <hi rend="italic">August</hi> 8, 1861</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: Your despatch of July 15 (No. 2) has been
                    received.</p>
                <p>Your conduct in regard to your presentation at court is approved.</p>
                <p>Your speech was discreet in its points and felicitous in expression. The Queen’s
                    reply is entirely satisfactory.</p>
                <p>I am, sir, your obedient servant,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>WILLIAM H. SEWARD.</signed>
                </closer>
                <postscript>
                    <p>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Carl Schurz</hi>, Esq., <hi rend="italic">&amp;c.,
                            &amp;c., &amp;c. Madrid</hi>.</p>
                </postscript>
            </div>
        </body>
